{
  "texts": [
    "We randomly selected 1000 questions each from SimpleQA and 2Wiki for efficient evaluation.",
    "Table 5 reports the short-form QA results.",
    "We find that DR Tulu performs competitively on short-form, verifiable QA benchmarks.",
    "Our SFT stage greatly improves over the Qwen3-8B + Our Search (dr-agent-lib) baseline, demonstrating the effectiveness of our SFT data for short-form QA.",
    "Interestingly, although the RL stage uses only long-form prompts and explicitly optimizes long-form generation quality, DR Tulu (RL) achieves further gains across datasets, improving the overall average by 4.4 points."
  ]
}